## Testing procedures & test data (Test Mode)
- Switch dashboard to Test mode to use TEST keys; test mode keys are suffixed/prefixed and should be obtained from Developers → API Keys in your Flutterwave dashboard [Flutterwave dashboard docs](https://flutterwave.com/gb/support/integrations/flutterwave-live-and-test-environments) .
- Standard Checkout test flow:
  1. Ensure RAVE_ENV=test and TEST_* keys set in `.env` [Authentication docs](https://developer.flutterwave.com/v3.0/docs/authentication) .
  2. Create a payment using the backend `/create-payment` endpoint; open the returned hosted `checkout_url`.
  3. Use test card numbers or mobile money credentials in the hosted page to simulate payments [Testing docs](https://developer.flutterwave.com/v3.0/docs/testing) .
  4. After redirect back to your frontend or via webhook, verify server-side using `/verify-payment` and Flutterwave verify endpoints.

